# 26 USC Section 1(j)(6) - Section 15 not to apply
# Prevents mid-year rate blending

status: boilerplate

text: """
(6) Section 15 not to apply

Section 15 shall not apply to any change in a rate of tax by reason of this subsection.
"""

# STATUS: boilerplate
# Section 15 normally requires blending tax rates when rates change mid-year.
# This provision exempts TCJA rate changes from that blending requirement.
# No computational content - just a special rule preventing section 15 application.
